"pid":"133501","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/133501/ccdbfe57-7872-4110-8878-4ab80989d700.png"},{"n":"Justin Lee Wynne","p":"Green Party","v":196,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133503","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/133503/73c8c7de-ff32-4c48-be61-22ecc8e4497c.png"},{"n":"Matthew Clifford Ainsworth","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":135,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133499"}]},{"ward":"Maze Hill","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hastings.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?XXR=0&ID=324&RPID=81024651","candidates":[{"n":"Karen Simnett","p":"Green Party","v":969,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"45097","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/45097.png","stmt":"I was born in the Buchanan hospital and grew up, went to school, work and play nearby. I’ve been a Hairdresser for twenty years; I may have cut yours.\r\n\r\nI want to see our local community thrive through sustainable reinvestment in the way we buy our food and energy, how we deal with our waste and how we travel. I believe by strengthening our local economy and infrastructure we make ourselves more resilient and less vulnerable to outside and often unpredictable forces.\r\n\r\nI am also a co-chair of Transition Town Hastings, a local community organization, exploring solutions to problems arising from climate change and environmental damage and expanding on the themes above to build a healthy environment to leave to our future generations.\r\n\r\nIn the spirit of Green Party Policy we are soon implementing a water bottle refill scheme to reduce plastic bottle waste, with an ambition to make Hastings a zero single-use plastic town."},{"n":"Rosie Murphy","p":"Reform UK","v":499,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133508"},{"n":"Rob Cooke","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":268,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"14660"},{"n":"Tim John Cairns Shand","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":223,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133509"},{"n":"Lee Joseph Grant","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":44,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"81380","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/81380-fc6ac298-4de7-4ffb-bd05-6d25d1fe679b.png"}]},{"ward":"Old Hastings","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hastings.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=61","candidates":[{"n":"Mike Frith","p":"Green Party","v":1064,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133511"},{"n":"James Edward Bacon","p":"Labour Party","v":640,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"14713","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/14713/f4ca7a41-06ef-4ba3-9ab1-af144a70384c.png"},{"n":"Steve Foot","p":"Reform UK","v":387,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133510"},{"n":"Ray Molloy","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":124,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"133512"}]},{"ward":"Ore","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hastings.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=61","candidates":[{"n":"Clem McCulloch","p":"Green Party","v":874,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"133516"},{"n":"Wojciech Duczmal","p":"Reform UK","v":471,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"133514"},{"n":"Kim Forward","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":167,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"133515"},{"n":"Brett Reginald McLean","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":113,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"107645"},{"n":"Vicky Wilson","p":"Independent","v":70,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133517","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/133517/7a19d8c7-e8b7-41fd-a496-4a9ace8e7025.png"}]},{"ward":"Silverhill","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hastings.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=61","candidates":[{"n":"Dulcie Reynolds","p":"Green Party","v":610,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112052"},{"n":"Ian Moore","p":"Reform UK","v":492,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133526"},{"n":"Margi O'Callaghan","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":327,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"133527","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/133527/8e44574e-4170-4462-a22e-27707d9e85ab.png","stmt":"Over the past few weeks, I’ve been out on your doorsteps, listening to residents, hearing your frustrations, and hearing your hopes for our community. Time and again, people tell me the same thing — they want councillors who work hard, listen, and put local people first.\n\nThat is exactly why I’m standing.\n\nI’m proud to have the backing of our local MP, and proud to stand for Labour with a clear plan for St Helens and Silverhill fixing potholes and pavements, improving playgrounds for families, tackling dog fouling and fly-tipping, and fighting for bus services that actually work for our community.\n\nThis election is about the kind of area we want to live in. Do we move forward with practical local action, or risk going backwards?\n\nI have the experience, the energy, and the determination to be a strong local voice for our community. On Thursday 7th May, I’m asking for your vote so together we can keep delivering for St Helens and Silverhill.\n\nVote Labour. Vote Margi. Putting local residents first."},{"n":"Nigel Sinden","p":"Independent","v":265,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"14738","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/14738/4884b5d7-4c91-43c4-a2da-2bd721da1396.png"},{"n":"Craig Steven Andrew","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":213,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"45093"}]},{"ward":"St Helens","seats":2,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hastings.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=61","candidates":[{"n":"Peter Anthony Clarke","p":"Reform UK","v":572,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133534"},{"n":"Andy Batsford","p":"Independent","v":544,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"14731","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/14731/fd556429-1c68-4137-a5f0-917e22c07bd1.png"},{"n":"Shaun Dowling","p":"Green Party","v":490,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"133535","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/133535/ccf00f67-dbf7-4675-a0e5-167659d86cc3.png","stmt":"Shaun is a local man born and raised in Hastings. He works in healthcare and has held previous roles in social care, giving him a clear understanding of the pressures facing local services, from GP access to adult social care provision. Having been involved in local politics from an early age, he has a strong grasp of the issues that matter most to residents—whether it’s the need for more affordable housing, tackling the rising cost of living, improving public transport links, or protecting vital community spaces.\nHe is committed to building on the progress made by the current Green-led council, particularly in areas such as environmental sustainability, support for local communities, and efforts to create a fairer local economy. Shaun believes more can be done to address inequality across the town, improve opportunities for young people, and ensure that regeneration benefits everyone—not just a few.\nAbove all, he is dedicated to making sure every resident has a voice in decision-making and that Hastings continues to move toward a greener, fairer, and more inclusive future.","bd":"1994"},{"n":"Jessica Townsend","p":"Green Party","v":462,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133539"},{"n":"Hazel Edith Vanbergen","p":"Reform UK","v":460,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133540"},{"n":"Barney Green","p":"Labour Party","v":320,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133536","stmt":"Standing to be a local Councillor in St Helens to maintain all of value in the ward, improving where he can for community benefit. \nA strong believer in the potential for good our town and ward can offer us when we connect, support each other and work together alongside our MP for Hastings and Rye Helena Dollimore.\n\n\"Promoted by Judy Rogers on behalf of Barnaby Green. Both at 84 Bohemia Road, St. Leonards on Sea TN37 6RN\"","tw":"\"HastingsRyeLab\"","url":"\"https://hastingsandryelabour.org.uk/\""},{"n":"Helen Martin","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":311,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133537"},{"n":"Howard Martin","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":249,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"133538"},{"n":"Stephen Butterton","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":229,"r":9,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112050"},{"n":"Bob Lloyd","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":164,"r":10,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"45147","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/45147-260a8fef-206d-4418-b437-8b5e5a9067b2.png"}]},{"ward":"Tressell","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hastings.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=61","candidates":[{"n":"Glenn Haffenden","p":"Green Party","v":921,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","